                labor fees. Additionally, older models or less common brands
                might present unique challenges, potentially increasing the time
                and effort needed for repairs.
              </p>
              <b>Service Provider Policies</b>
              <p>
                The policies of the service provider can also impact labor
                costs. Some companies may charge a flat rate for specific types
                of repairs, while others might have an hourly rate.
                Additionally, emergency or after-hours repairs can incur higher
                labor costs due to the urgency and inconvenience involved.
              </p>

